WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:02.666 --> 00:00:04.133
Do you have this kind of trouble?

00:00:04.133 --> 00:00:06.133
You

00:00:06.133 --> 00:00:07.733
went out with your good friend for a few days, and when you came back, you

00:00:07.733 --> 00:00:09.933
found that she was as fair as she could be,

00:00:09.933 --> 00:00:11.666
but you were much darker.

00:00:11.700 --> 00:00:13.600
So you looked up tips online and

00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:15.233
bought a lot of whitening essences,

00:00:15.233 --> 00:00:16.300
but you used them all up, but your face

00:00:16.300 --> 00:00:17.333
still didn’t get whiter

00:00:17.466 --> 00:00:19.266
. Or, there is a situation like this:

00:00:19.266 --> 00:00:20.866
you have been very busy at work recently,

00:00:20.866 --> 00:00:22.700
working overtime and staying up late a lot,

00:00:22.700 --> 00:00:23.633
and your face is

00:00:23.633 --> 00:00:26.033
very dull and yellow,

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:28.133
so you looked up tips online and

00:00:28.233 --> 00:00:29.866
bought a popular product,

00:00:29.866 --> 00:00:30.533
but after

00:00:30.533 --> 00:00:32.433
using it, not only did your face not get whiter

00:00:32.433 --> 00:00:33.800
, but your skin also got chapped and

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:35.866
allergic. There is another situation

00:00:35.866 --> 00:00:38.400
, that is, you went out in the sun today

00:00:38.400 --> 00:00:41.000
, and your skin turned red like a red shrimp.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.266
You thought it would be fine after a few days,

00:00:43.266 --> 00:00:44.633
but after a few days,

00:00:44.633 --> 00:00:46.400
your face was red and black, and it

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:47.866
looked very dirty.

00:00:47.866 --> 00:00:50.066
What should we do at this time?

00:00:50.100 --> 00:00:51.133
There is also a situation

00:00:51.133 --> 00:00:52.300
like

00:00:52.433 --> 00:00:54.900
My skin is not very dark, but

00:00:55.033 --> 00:00:58.033
I can never find the right foundation for me.

00:00:58.100 --> 00:00:59.300
I buy the natural color, but

00:00:59.300 --> 00:01:00.733
this foundation is darker than me.

00:01:00.800 --> 00:01:01.866
I buy the cold porcelain white, but

00:01:01.866 --> 00:01:03.900
this foundation is much whiter than me.

00:01:04.033 --> 00:01:06.800
So is my skin color white or dark?

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:08.666
What kind of products should I use?

00:01:09.066 --> 00:01:10.600
The reason why we can't find the answers to

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:12.300
the questions I just mentioned

00:01:12.300 --> 00:01:14.000
and why they are not solved

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.600
is because we have never thought about

00:01:16.600 --> 00:01:19.300
how we got darker.

00:01:19.366 --> 00:01:22.433
Only by analyzing how we got darker

00:01:22.433 --> 00:01:25.266
can we find a way to whiten it back.

00:01:25.266 --> 00:01:29.233
What I want to tell you today is to help you analyze

00:01:29.233 --> 00:01:31.866
what type of darkening physique you have. I'd like

00:01:31.866 --> 00:01:34.833
to say in advance that this issue will be a little long

00:01:34.833 --> 00:01:36.066
and dry.

00:01:36.600 --> 00:01:39.000
I will divide it into several aspects, such as basic principles,

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:40.233
whitening

00:01:40.266 --> 00:01:43.700
types , and how to choose products.

00:01:43.700 --> 00:01:45.433
Today

00:01:45.433 --> 00:01:49.200
's topic is the 16-type whitening method. If you

00:01:55.733 --> 00:01:57.233
want to know how to whiten your skin,

00:01:57.233 --> 00:02:00.533
you must first know how you get darker and

00:02:00.533 --> 00:02:03.100
what the whole process of your darkening is.

00:02:03.100 --> 00:02:05.466
This basic knowledge is actually very important

00:02:05.466 --> 00:02:08.400
because few people pay attention to it.

00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:10.133
The key to your whitening

00:02:10.133 --> 00:02:13.900
is actually buried in the whole process of darkening.

00:02:14.266 --> 00:02:15.533
First of all,

00:02:15.533 --> 00:02:17.800
all types of darkening

00:02:17.800 --> 00:02:21.066
start with a stimulus.

00:02:21.066 --> 00:02:22.066
This stimulus

00:02:22.066 --> 00:02:24.200
can include external and internal

00:02:24.200 --> 00:02:25.000
factors.

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.033
For example, being exposed to sunlight,

00:02:27.033 --> 00:02:28.600
staying up late, eating chili peppers,

00:02:28.600 --> 00:02:29.300
air pollution

00:02:29.300 --> 00:02:30.466
, etc. What about the internal factors

00:02:30.466 --> 00:02:31.800
? For example, you

00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:33.333
have been under too much stress recently,

00:02:33.333 --> 00:02:34.700
have endocrine disorders, have

00:02:34.700 --> 00:02:35.633
an irregular diet

00:02:35.633 --> 00:02:36.400
, or have caught

00:02:36.400 --> 00:02:37.300
a cold or are sick.

00:02:37.300 --> 00:02:39.066
These are all internal reasons

00:02:39.066 --> 00:02:40.633
. Whether it is an external

00:02:40.633 --> 00:02:41.933
or internal reason,

00:02:41.933 --> 00:02:45.066
it is very important for the body. A

00:02:45.066 --> 00:02:45.866
stimulus will

00:02:45.866 --> 00:02:47.600
cause different damage and effects to

00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:50.066
our skin cells

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:51.500
. These stimuli

00:02:51.500 --> 00:02:54.100
will produce different substances and signals

00:02:54.100 --> 00:02:56.733
. There are related receptors on our skin

00:02:56.733 --> 00:02:58.266
to receive these stimuli

00:02:58.266 --> 00:03:00.800
. In fact, there is a physical difference.

00:03:00.800 --> 00:03:03.533
Some people are particularly sensitive

00:03:03.533 --> 00:03:04.666
to stimuli,

00:03:04.700 --> 00:03:05.433
while others

00:03:05.433 --> 00:03:07.000
are a little slower and more

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:08.333
tolerant.

00:03:08.833 --> 00:03:10.133
When our skin cells

00:03:10.133 --> 00:03:11.700
receive this stimulus,

00:03:11.700 --> 00:03:15.066
two phenomena will occur in our body at the same time.

00:03:15.266 --> 00:03:18.400
One is that the collagen in our skin will

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:22.700
be denatured and decomposed directly due to these stimuli.

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:24.866
The phenomenon visible to our naked eyes

00:03:24.866 --> 00:03:27.033
is that although the skin cannot be said to be black

00:03:27.033 --> 00:03:28.866
, it is not so transparent

00:03:28.866 --> 00:03:31.033
and looks very dull and yellow.

00:03:31.300 --> 00:03:32.600
The other phenomenon

00:03:32.600 --> 00:03:35.500
is that our skin After being stimulated, cells

00:03:35.500 --> 00:03:38.633
will send signals to melanocytes

00:03:38.633 --> 00:03:40.200
to generate melanin

00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:42.733
because the body believes that melanin can protect our

00:03:42.733 --> 00:03:45.233
skin cells from the damage of these stimuli

00:03:45.333 --> 00:03:46.066
.

00:03:46.066 --> 00:03:48.433
There is actually a particularly interesting phenomenon here

00:03:48.433 --> 00:03:50.666
. After our epidermal cells are stimulated,

00:03:50.666 --> 00:03:51.833
they will produce melanin

00:03:51.833 --> 00:03:52.333
, right?

00:03:52.333 --> 00:03:54.733
Normally, you send a signal once and that's it,

00:03:54.733 --> 00:03:56.866
but it

00:03:56.866 --> 00:04:00.000
won't stop

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:01.433
until it sees enough melanin

00:04:01.666 --> 00:04:03.100
. This is like

00:04:03.100 --> 00:04:05.633
going to a restaurant to order food,

00:04:05.633 --> 00:04:08.833
and as long as the waiter doesn't bring the dish to the table,

00:04:08.833 --> 00:04:11.033
you keep ordering, ordering, and ordering.

00:04:11.033 --> 00:04:13.000
What is the result?

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:14.300
When the dish comes,

00:04:14.300 --> 00:04:15.466
you find that you ordered too much.

00:04:15.666 --> 00:04:17.300
This is just like our skin

00:04:17.333 --> 00:04:19.200
. By the time you realize that you have become darker,

00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:21.000
you already have too much melanin.

00:04:21.333 --> 00:04:22.433
To summarize briefly,

00:04:22.433 --> 00:04:24.466
these two steps occur simultaneously

00:04:24.466 --> 00:04:26.866
but also promote each other.

00:04:27.066 --> 00:04:29.533
After collagen decomposes and denatures,

00:04:29.533 --> 00:04:32.866
it actually pollutes the cell environment. After

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:35.200
the epidermal cells sense this pollution,

00:04:35.200 --> 00:04:37.300
they will promote the secretion of more signals

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:39.133
to promote the production of melanin.

00:04:39.133 --> 00:04:41.100
The final result is that

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:43.633
we produce more melanin.

00:04:43.900 --> 00:04:45.666
Okay, let's continue.

00:04:45.666 --> 00:04:49.133
The following is the process of melanin production.

00:04:49.633 --> 00:04:52.300
The raw material for the start of melanin production is

00:04:52.300 --> 00:04:53.833
called tyrosine.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.933
Then we introduce a hydroxyl group to tyrosine

00:04:56.933 --> 00:04:58.300
to form dopa,

00:04:58.400 --> 00:05:01.900
and then oxidize the two hydroxyl groups of dopa to form dopaquinone.

00:05:02.133 --> 00:05:03.800
Later, dopaquinone

00:05:03.800 --> 00:05:07.133
will produce two types of melanin at the same time.

00:05:07.200 --> 00:05:08.866
One is called eumelanin

00:05:08.866 --> 00:05:10.700
and the other is called pheomelanin.

00:05:10.733 --> 00:05:13.300
Eumelanin is the main pigment for dark skin

00:05:13.300 --> 00:05:15.500
. For example, black people

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:18.300
have a skin color dominated by eumelanin

00:05:18.466 --> 00:05:20.700
, while pheomelanin is dominant in lighter skin.

00:05:20.700 --> 00:05:22.633
Caucasians

00:05:22.633 --> 00:05:24.200
have a skin color dominated by pheomelanin.

00:05:24.200 --> 00:05:25.433
Asians

00:05:25.433 --> 00:05:27.933
are a compromise, with both eumelanin

00:05:27.933 --> 00:05:28.866
and pheomelanin

00:05:28.866 --> 00:05:30.866
distributed in different proportions.

00:05:31.066 --> 00:05:33.833
The process I just described sounds complicated

00:05:33.866 --> 00:05:36.833
, but it's just like making a gift cup.

00:05:36.866 --> 00:05:38.133
First,

00:05:38.133 --> 00:05:40.400
we put a label on it, then

00:05:40.633 --> 00:05:42.333
tie a ribbon on it

00:05:42.333 --> 00:05:45.866
, and then package it into flower boxes of different colors

00:05:45.866 --> 00:05:47.066
and sell it to different people.

00:05:47.400 --> 00:05:49.066
I have to explain

00:05:49.066 --> 00:05:51.700
why I explain the process of melanin production

00:05:51.700 --> 00:05:52.900
in such detail.

00:05:52.900 --> 00:05:55.666
This is because it will help you understand

00:05:55.666 --> 00:05:57.666
the role of

00:05:57.666 --> 00:06:00.266
our whitening ingredients .

00:06:00.333 --> 00:06:02.266
For example, What did VC do?

00:06:02.266 --> 00:06:05.266
VC took off the ribbon on the cup and threw

00:06:05.266 --> 00:06:07.400
it away. After it was taken off and thrown away, there was no ribbon left

00:06:07.400 --> 00:06:08.633
. Did it have to continue tying it?

00:06:08.633 --> 00:06:10.433
So it continued to tie a ribbon

00:06:10.433 --> 00:06:11.233
and then threw it away.

00:06:11.233 --> 00:06:12.133
Then it tied it again, threw it again, tied it

00:06:12.133 --> 00:06:13.033
again, threw it again, and threw it again.

00:06:13.033 --> 00:06:15.133
So it kept at this step and could not

00:06:15.133 --> 00:06:15.833
move to the next

00:06:15.833 --> 00:06:17.133
step. Melanin could not be produced,

00:06:17.133 --> 00:06:18.300
the production efficiency became low,

00:06:18.300 --> 00:06:19.433
the melanin became less, and

00:06:19.433 --> 00:06:20.266
you became whiter.

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:23.100
Okay, now the melanin production is completed

00:06:23.233 --> 00:06:25.600
, but as a factory,

00:06:25.600 --> 00:06:28.400
the melanocyte has no warehouse

00:06:28.400 --> 00:06:30.433
, it does not store these melanins.

00:06:30.433 --> 00:06:31.866
Once the production is completed,

00:06:31.866 --> 00:06:34.633
it will spit it out through exocytosis.

00:06:35.333 --> 00:06:37.833
This step is the release of melanin.

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:39.500
It will spit in the direction of whoever

00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:40.933
sends it a signal

00:06:40.933 --> 00:06:43.800
, that is, towards the epidermal cells.

00:06:43.866 --> 00:06:47.500
But spitting it out into the environment of the cell

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:49.133
is useless.

00:06:49.133 --> 00:06:52.900
The epidermal cells must also have a receiver

00:06:52.900 --> 00:06:53.933
to pick it up and

00:06:53.933 --> 00:06:55.066
bring it to their own part.

00:06:55.066 --> 00:06:57.900
This step is called the reception of epidermal cells.

00:06:58.000 --> 00:06:59.866
The two steps of spitting out and receiving

00:06:59.866 --> 00:07:02.666
are also very critical.

00:07:02.700 --> 00:07:03.666
This step

00:07:03.666 --> 00:07:06.900
is equivalent to the packaged cup being delivered to the person

00:07:06.900 --> 00:07:08.066
who placed the order.

00:07:08.066 --> 00:07:10.266
After our epidermal cells

00:07:10.266 --> 00:07:12.133
continue to receive melanin,

00:07:12.133 --> 00:07:13.600
they enter the next

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:16.266
step, which is the deposition and aggregation of melanin.

00:07:16.300 --> 00:07:17.900
At this stage,

00:07:17.900 --> 00:07:20.066
there are actually two forms of expression.

00:07:20.233 --> 00:07:23.233
One is called uniform aggregation,

00:07:23.366 --> 00:07:24.266
which is manifested

00:07:24.266 --> 00:07:27.066
as our uniform skin color becoming darker.

00:07:27.066 --> 00:07:27.933
The other

00:07:27.933 --> 00:07:29.733
is called uneven aggregation

00:07:29.933 --> 00:07:32.733
, which means we get spots or acne scars.

00:07:32.900 --> 00:07:36.266
Which specific type of aggregation you will have

00:07:36.266 --> 00:07:38.233
is actually determined by your genes

00:07:38.233 --> 00:07:39.500
, not the ingredients

00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:41.066
or the stimulus. After

00:07:41.466 --> 00:07:42.466
these melanins

00:07:42.466 --> 00:07:44.500
accumulate in our epidermal cells,

00:07:44.500 --> 00:07:46.233
the process is not over yet,

00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:47.700
because our epidermal cells

00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:50.400
also have their own natural life cycle.

00:07:50.400 --> 00:07:52.133
They will gradually age and die

00:07:52.133 --> 00:07:53.400
to become stratum corneum

00:07:53.400 --> 00:07:56.133
and eventually fall off and leave our body

00:07:56.133 --> 00:07:57.400
. In this process,

00:07:57.400 --> 00:08:00.533
they also carry melanin all the time.

00:08:00.533 --> 00:08:01.433
So eventually

00:08:01.433 --> 00:08:04.633
our melanin will enter the dead stratum corneum

00:08:04.633 --> 00:08:06.866
and eventually leave our body.

00:08:07.066 --> 00:08:09.066
When the stratum corneum takes our melanin

00:08:09.066 --> 00:08:10.200
away

00:08:10.200 --> 00:08:14.100
, The entire melanin production and metabolism process

00:08:14.133 --> 00:08:15.633
is considered to be complete.

00:08:16.066 --> 00:08:18.733
Okay, the entire process of darkening is introduced here. It is

00:08:18.733 --> 00:08:20.000
very long and complicated.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:21.133
It doesn’t matter if you can’t remember

00:08:21.133 --> 00:08:23.400
it . Just have a general impression.

00:08:23.400 --> 00:08:24.500
Because we are

00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:28.733
going to use this 9-step darkening process as the theoretical basis

00:08:28.733 --> 00:08:31.033
to introduce today’s highlight

00:08:31.033 --> 00:08:33.633
, which is the four types of darkening.

00:08:38.033 --> 00:08:39.266
This darkening type

00:08:39.266 --> 00:08:40.200
is not

00:08:40.200 --> 00:08:42.466
based on a single chemical theory.

00:08:42.466 --> 00:08:45.200
It is based on my more than ten years of clinical experience. At the same time

00:08:45.200 --> 00:08:47.066
, I checked the theory and

00:08:47.066 --> 00:08:50.700
finally summarized the four types of darkening constitutions.

00:08:50.733 --> 00:08:52.800
These four types are not

00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:53.633
ranked in order or priority,

00:08:53.633 --> 00:08:55.700
namely, tanning type

00:08:55.700 --> 00:08:57.866
, dull type, red and black type

00:08:57.866 --> 00:08:59.300
, and yellow type

00:08:59.400 --> 00:09:00.733
. Let’s talk about sunburn first. A typical example of this type of physique

00:09:00.800 --> 00:09:03.700
is what we mentioned at the beginning:

00:09:03.700 --> 00:09:05.066
you go out with a friend,

00:09:05.066 --> 00:09:06.266
she comes back quite white, but

00:09:06.266 --> 00:09:07.300
you are two shades darker.

00:09:07.300 --> 00:09:09.133
This type of physique manifests itself

00:09:09.133 --> 00:09:12.933
in that you tan much faster than others.

00:09:12.933 --> 00:09:14.433
The characteristic of this type of physique

00:09:14.433 --> 00:09:16.066
is that

00:09:16.066 --> 00:09:19.300
the sixth and seventh steps of the nine-step tanning process we just introduced,

00:09:19.300 --> 00:09:22.466
namely, the release and reception of melanin,

00:09:22.533 --> 00:09:24.600
are faster than others.

00:09:24.666 --> 00:09:28.033
Why doesn't it mean that you produce melanin faster than others? Let

00:09:28.066 --> 00:09:30.033
me give you a timeline.

00:09:30.100 --> 00:09:31.600
When you receive the stimulus

00:09:31.600 --> 00:09:33.633
and start sending the signal,

00:09:33.633 --> 00:09:36.800
it takes about 1 to 24 hours

00:09:36.866 --> 00:09:39.866
, and the entire process of melanin production

00:09:39.866 --> 00:09:43.100
takes about 24 to 72 hours.

00:09:43.266 --> 00:09:44.433
That is to say,

00:09:44.433 --> 00:09:47.733
after you receive the stimulation of being sunburned, it

00:09:47.733 --> 00:09:49.666
will take at least two or three days

00:09:49.666 --> 00:09:51.466
for you to notice

00:09:51.766 --> 00:09:53.733
that you have become darker. For example, if you go sunbathing in the morning and

00:09:53.733 --> 00:09:55.666
come back in the evening and see that you are darker,

00:09:55.666 --> 00:09:58.466
it is definitely not the melanin that has been produced , but

00:09:58.466 --> 00:10:00.833
the melanin that has been produced in the skin

00:10:00.833 --> 00:10:02.066
but has not yet been transported

00:10:02.066 --> 00:10:04.066
and received. The melanin

00:10:04.100 --> 00:10:05.866
is quickly mobilized,

00:10:05.866 --> 00:10:07.866
released, and absorbed,

00:10:07.866 --> 00:10:10.500
so it will tan so quickly.

00:10:10.500 --> 00:10:12.600
So what should people with this kind

00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:14.733
of constitution do? They should focus on steps 6 and 7

00:10:14.733 --> 00:10:17.900
, that is, the release and reception of melanin,

00:10:17.900 --> 00:10:21.500
to block and reduce the excitement and speed of these two steps.

00:10:21.900 --> 00:10:24.600
There are two ingredients that are particularly suitable for this kind of constitution

00:10:24.600 --> 00:10:26.633
, namely niacinamide and EGCG.

00:10:26.666 --> 00:10:28.800
What does niacinamide do?

00:10:28.800 --> 00:10:30.666
It blocks exocytosis,

00:10:30.666 --> 00:10:33.200
that is, it covers the mouth of the melanocyte.

00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:34.900
If the melanin cannot be expelled

00:10:34.900 --> 00:10:35.866
, it cannot be received, and

00:10:35.866 --> 00:10:36.666
you cannot get darker.

00:10:36.900 --> 00:10:38.333
What does EGCG do? EGCG

00:10:38.333 --> 00:10:40.333
cuts off the little hand that

00:10:40.333 --> 00:10:42.800
the epidermal cell uses to receive melanin

00:10:42.800 --> 00:10:45.600
. If it cannot reach your own cells,

00:10:45.600 --> 00:10:46.666
you cannot get darker.

00:10:46.666 --> 00:10:47.500
Simply put,

